ast.comment: A library to create tower defense games. See main for example.

WhfTHpYcn6Ba3gEVvTaAhabV.text: 'tower defense' is a library to help building classic tower defense games.

aM2EFh9bRNABuI9bcuxS6vXx.text: You should start by initializing the library in your 'main' action. Pass your game board to the 'initialize' action of the library.

xf2yCz914tCdVF2NibHj1nTm.text: In order to create towers, first create a sprite - it can be any kind of sprite. Then register this sprite as a tower in the library.

nR2h4cTYn2ymt8hhpMipixo5.text: Towers are static elements in the library. You should not move them
Attention, towers should not be moving elements in the library. You should not move them
Attention, towers should not be moving.

xf2yCz914tCdVF2NibHj1nTm.text: In order to create towers, first create a sprite - it can be any kind of sprite. Then register this sprite as a tower in the library. Attention, towers should not be moving.

In order to create towers, first create a sprite - it can be any kind of sprite. Then register this sprite as a tower in the library. Attention, towers should not be moved after being added. The arguments of 'add tower' specify the range, power, reload delay and color of the bullets. You can add more towers at any point in time.

xfqDOnya44Cb8nzbclEl96LI.text: This code simulates what usually happens in the event gameloop. After you call 'evolve' on the board, you need to call 'evolve' of the library to update the state of the towers and bullets.

uVazEI2mjQciOKp459sXTjJa.text: The library works with a board, so we start by creating one.
